membership:
Eurochild is member of the following EU umbrella networks:&#xd;
- Social Platform&#xd;
- European Public Health Alliance&#xd;
- European Anti-Poverty Network&#xd;
- Liaison Group of Civil Society Organisations with the European Economic &amp; Social Committee (EESC)&#xd;
&#xd;
Other informal alliances where Eurochild is active include:&#xd;
- The European Expert Group on the transition from institutional to communitybased care&#xd;
- The Child Rights Action Group an informal group of international NGOs &amp; membership networks&#xd;
- The EU Alliance for Investing in Children&#xd;
&#xd;
The Opening Doors for Europe’s Children campaign is a partnership with Home &amp; Homes for Children, SOS Children’s Villages International, International Foster Care Organisation &amp; FICE Europe.&#xd;
&#xd;
Eurochild has a close working relationship with UNICEF and the Council of Europe. Eurochild is an active member of the global child rights network Child Rights Connect.&#xd;
&#xd;
Eurochild has strong relations with sister children’s rights networks, in particular ChildPact &amp; the European Network of Ombudsmen for Children.
